results.raw: Suspect in Custody After Homicide, Setting Woman on Fire at 1700 Wynne Ave, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55108
results.rawLocation: 1700 Wynne Ave, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55108
results.title: Suspect in Custody After Homicide, Setting Woman on Fire

-MyCuGlvqooTrgpUDDJS.text: Police are responding to an unconfirmed report that a person lit a woman on fire.

-MyCv8MT3-oZiyvVXZmN.text: The suspect is described as a 40-year-old White man wearing an orange knitted hat and a work vest.

nib.text:
Police detained a suspect in the murder of a woman in the Langford Park area Tuesday afternoon, officials said.

At around 9 a.m., police responded to a report of a person on fire at a warehouse in the 1700 block of Wynne Avenue.

Upon arrival, officers discovered an unconscious woman who had been badly burnt. 

Medics responded and pronounced her deceased at the scene.

Homicide detectives began investigating and identified a suspect, 47-year-old Patrick Morris Simmons of Bloomington, who had a prior relationship with the victim.

 St. Paul police contacted Bloomington police who detained the suspect in their jurisdiction this morning after his home was set on fire.

Simmons was taken into custody by the SPPD and charged with the murder of the victim. 

Homicide detectives are continuing to investigate. 

This marks the 11th homicide of 2022 in St. Paul.
